@Neel, @Achyut Saxena here are some more logo variations from me and Arina. She wanted to explore some visuals that will tie up the logo with the video industry, by using key frames and angle symbols that are prevalent in editing software. In a more general sense this could mean not only video editing, but story editing, and the creative process itself.

From my end, I wanted to build on a existing 'attn co' variant. And I think it can be taken a step further and include the full word with all unnecessary character taken out, while still retaining the word readability. To show that Attention as a creative company is brave enough to use only those tools that are needed to convey the essence of the story without any additional distracting noise. 

The key frames and a pointer symbols are used here to replace period symbols and bringing some video industry authenticity.
